HEADWORD: Neckweed
<hw>Neck"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An American annual weed (<spn>veronica
peregrina</spn>), with small white flowers and a roundish pod.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The hemp; -- so called as furnishing ropes for hanging
criminals.</def> <rj><au>Dr. Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necrobiosis</ent>⟦br⟧
